  "metadata": {
    "title": "Beetroot, Caraway and Goat\u2019s Cheese Bread",
    "description": "Making a bread which requires no yeast and no kneading has got to be the definition of simple! The texture is more \u2018cakey\u2019 as a result, best eaten with some salted butter (rather than used to make sandwiches). If you are warming it through, do so in the oven rather than in the toaster, as it\u2019s quite crumbly. Once baked, it will keep in an airtight container for a week or in the freezer for up to a month \u2013 thaw before slicing and grilling.",
    "servings": 8,
    "recipeType": "base",
    "notes": [
      "Making a bread which requires no yeast and no kneading has got to be the definition of simple! The texture is more \u2018cakey\u2019 as a result, best eaten with some salted butter (rather than used to make sandwiches). If you are warming it through, do so in the oven rather than in the toaster, as it\u2019s quite crumbly. Once baked, it will keep in an airtight container for a week or in the freezer for up to a month \u2013 thaw before slicing and grilling.",
      "\u00a9 Yotam Ottolenghi 2021 \u2014 Photography \u00a9 PEDEN + MUNK"
